Commentary: round the wicket, high arm and looped on leg stump, Banton leans out and tucks it square off the pads
pushed through, flat and quick and heading leg side, YJB closes the face and gets a leading edge to off
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Bairstow, no run

Commentary: whipped off the stumps, Bairstow wants two and comes barrellling back, makes it home as Rizwan breaks the stumps
dotted on off, YJB punches back to the bowler's left
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Bairstow, no run

Commentary: thumps it back, taken in his follow through! Sharp catch, Imad only just held on in the end, but he makes sure by clutching it to his body... and Bairstow is off. Connected well with his drive but sent it straight back at the bowler around mid-calf - very fashionable - and Imad held on
Dismissal_text: JM Bairstow c & b Imad Wasim 2 (4b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50.00

Commentary: over the wicket, angled in towards the lefty who pokes into the covers
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Malan, no run

Commentary: pitched up, 86mph/138kph and Banton whips the hands through a driven shot to midwicket
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Banton, no run

Commentary: length, 83mph/134kph and angling across, Banton has a little flirt
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Banton, no run

Commentary: dug in, good bouncer from Afridi, high over the ducking Banton
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Banton, no run

Commentary: good length, 86mph/138kph in the channel, slide awaaaaaaay Oasis-style as Banton swings at it and misses
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Banton, no run

Commentary: on the pads, Banton deals with this one adroitly, clipped fine for England's first boundary! Been a quiet start by their normally gung ho standards
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Banton, FOUR runs

Commentary: dropped! Dolly at slip from Iftikhar Ahmed, Banton gets a life... Loose fiddle at an 87mph length ball, thick edge carried at a nice height, but he shelled it
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Banton, no run

Commentary: fired in from over the wicket, tucked to leg
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Malan, no run

Commentary: flat on middle and off, Malan works it down the ground through mid-on
round the wicket, tossed up straight and Banton sweeps, top-edges it over short fine leg, will run away for three
pushed through quickly outside off, Malan reverse-sweeps for one
fired in as Banton looks to skip down, jammed into the ground towards mid-off for another single
on the stumps, no width to work with and Malan does well to flick into a gap leg side for a couple
length ball, slapped into the covers coming forwards, picks out a fielder
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Banton, no run

Commentary: slower ball outside off, Banton ruins this through gully for one
back of a length, 84mph/135kph and Malan takes it on the splice looking to work across the line
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Malan, no run

Commentary: hits the pitch, 84mph on middle and leg and nudged into a gap at midwicket for two more
back of a length and skidding through outside off as Malan tries to clatter through the off side and misses
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Malan, no run

Commentary: pace off again, on the stumps and clipped in the air, shout of 'catch!' from Amir but it doesn't carry to deep square leg
over the wicket, pitched up around off stump, punched down the ground
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Malan, no run

Commentary: short of a length, 83mph/134kph and Malan picks it, cracks a pull to deep backward square leg! Only England's second boundary of the innings
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Malan, FOUR runs

Commentary: spears in the yorker, Malan gets a good chunk of it driving back down the pitch but straight into the stumps. Banton was back, in case of a fingertip from Shaheen
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Malan, no run

Commentary: cutter, full in the slot outside off, big ole swing and a miss from Malan
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Malan, no run

Commentary: fires in another full-bunger, Malan digs it out
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Malan, 1 run

Commentary: pitched up around middle and leg, nudged off the pads for one more
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Banton, 1 run

Commentary: short, pace off as Banton steps out, can only chip it over the leg side for one
dug in short as Malan hangs back, good bouncer and he elects to let it through
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Malan, no run

Commentary: length, another cutter and Malan is foxed, swings it away off the toe of the bat through backward square leg
in the channel, angles the bat face and runs one to third man
pitched up and tonked through midwicket for four! Bottom hand taking over, whipped uppishly past the man in the ring but it landed safely and skipped away
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Banton, FOUR runs

Commentary: length and swung away to deep square leg for one
short of a length, 86mph/138kph and sliding down the leg side
88mph, back of a length outside off, Banton swipes it through point to the boundary rider

leg-stump yorker, 89mph/143kph and Malan takes it on the boot, Banton calls him through as it deflects into the gully region... and Babar has reviewed this. Pitching outside leg might be the main issue; and UltraEdge has also picked up some bat. So Pakistan will lose one of their two reviews
short outside off, cross-seamer and Banton swats a pull through midwicket
pitched up, 90mph/145kph outside off, chops down for one through mid-on
full in the channel, slower ball and Banton carts it towards mid-on
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Banton, no run

Commentary: short outside off, 87mph/139kph and Banton mistimes a pull down into his boots, Malan scampers through as Rauf runs down to field
honked over deep midwicket! Banton clicks up through the gears, rolls out the slog-sweep and connects with it perfectly, high and handsome towards the shorter boundary
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Banton, SIX runs

Commentary: pushed through flat outside off and Banton rocks back to cut to the sweeper
legbreak, slows his pace up, Malan attempts to reverse-sweep and takes it on the pads... got quite a big stride in
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Malan, no run

Commentary: flat outside off and Malan cuts one off the back foot
tries to come down, Shadab throws it wider, spinning away and he toe-ends into the covers
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Banton, no run

Commentary: floated up outside off, Banton drops back and slaps this through point for one more to the sweeper
pitched up, 86mph/138kph and nudged square, deep midwicket has to race in and they get two
full length, slower ball and Banton steps across, waits for it and pings to deep midwicket
length on the stumps, 86mph and Malan heaves to leg, gets one off the inside half of the bat
brings out the sweet trolley, lollipops a cutter over his shoulder and away! Cute from Banton, picking the undefended part of the ground and he got a good connection on it
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Banton, FOUR runs

Commentary: pitched up towards the blockhole and dug out into the off side
full on off, skelped through extra cover! Malan finds the rope with a classical drive, full flowing bat
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Malan, FOUR runs

Commentary: fetched! Banton goes down town from the first ball of the over again, just enough to clear long-on!
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Banton, SIX runs

Commentary: clattered over the pickets again! Unfurls a monstrous slog-sweep and this flies flat into the empty seats... Banton is firing now, already on a T20I best, closing in on fifty
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Banton, SIX runs

Commentary: calamity! Two batsmen at the same end! Malan came racing down but Banton wasn't going anywhere... squeezed towards backward point, the fielder, Mohammad Hafeez, was in pretty quickly. Didn't look like there was a run there. Breakthrough for Pakistan
Dismissal_text: DJ Malan run out (Mohammad Hafeez/Shadab Khan) 23 (23b 2x4 0x6) SR: 100.00

Commentary: darted in and he picks out a man in the ring
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Banton, no run

Commentary: tosses up the legbreak, Banton rocks back and slaps a cut through the ring
flighted, Morgan goes reversy... swished up and over backward point for four! Loves that funky stuff, whipped away first ball
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Morgan, FOUR runs

Commentary: round the wicket, dobbed outside off and Banton cuts, that's his half-century - first time he's got there in T20Is
slows his pace up, tapped into the covers
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Morgan, no run

Commentary: Morgan hoicks his third ball for six! Plants the front foot and his with Imad's angle from over the wicket, really collared the shot
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Morgan, SIX runs

Commentary: flat on middle and off, no room to free the arm, belted down the ground
skips out, creams a drive over wide long-on! Another sweetly struck six and the Banton bus is truly motoring now!
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Banton, SIX runs

Commentary: shouts of 'catch!' as he hits down the ground, not got hold of it but bounces short of long-on
scooped! Banton get it over short fine leg and away! Banton looking to go all around the park
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Banton, FOUR runs

Commentary: pitched up on the stumps and shovelled into the leg side for a couple, brings up the England 1o0
scoops this for six! Outrageous from Banton, walking across outside off stump, using the pace and just a flick of those wrists - honed on the hockey pitch - and it sails all the way!
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Banton, SIX runs

Commentary: nearly chops on! 80mph/129kph and skidding on outside off, Banton kabs down on it late
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Banton, no run

Commentary: slower ball, Banton again moving across outside off, can only dink it through mid-on with a checked shot
length on off, Morgan waits for it and dabs towards backward point
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Morgan, no run

Commentary: steps out straight away, Shadab drags it down and gets some spin, toe-ended through extra cover
tossed up and flipped through the leg side

flight and spin, Banton goes hard across the line, top-edges to extra cover! Revenge for Shadab, who was threatened with being taken to the cleaners but mops up nicely, removing England's young gun with one that gripped
Dismissal_text: T Banton c Imad Wasim b Shadab Khan 71 (42b 4x4 5x6) SR: 169.04

Commentary: pushes the googly across Morgan, who toes it towards point
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Morgan, no run

Commentary: tossed up, again pushed wide and Morgan chops in front of square for one
floated up and Moeen is across to stab one through the off side
stroked through the covers! Moeen at his languid best, hits inside out for four
Commentary_short: Iftikhar Ahmed to Ali, FOUR runs

Commentary: sliced into the off side, lands short of the fielder
Commentary_short: Iftikhar Ahmed to Ali, no run

Commentary: dragged down and wheeled through midwicket for one
tossed up and pinged down the ground to long-off
floated on the pads, Moeen taps into a gap at mid-on

slung down full, goes for the sweep... pinned in front! Finger goes up with Morgan rooted on off stump, Iftikhar does come good with the ball in hand. Hitting middle of middle, according to ball-tracking
Dismissal_text: EJG Morgan lbw b Iftikhar Ahmed 14 (10b 1x4 1x6) SR: 140.00

Commentary: tossed up and Moeen sweeps, doesn't get a great connection but picks up one
flighted legbreak, Billings goes deep but picks out extra cover with a forceful cut
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Billings, no run

Commentary: tossed up and driven coming down, single to long-off

taken on the rebound by Rizwan! Moeen falls cheaply to the legspinner, trying to cut one skidding on outside off, thick deflection but the keeper was following it like a bloodhound with a scent, couldn't take it cleanly but flung himself forward to cling on and send Moeen back!
Dismissal_text: MM Ali c †Mohammad Rizwan b Shadab Khan 8 (7b 1x4 0x6) SR: 114.28

Commentary: pushed through, maybe the wrong'un on middle and leg, jabbed away from the crease
flat leggie outside off, Billings goes back and finds backward point
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Billings, no run

Commentary: round the wicket, flat outside off and cut off the back foot
sliding leg side, chipped into the gap at deep midwicket

quick, spinning away past the bat - and Rizwan does the rest! Gregory walks past one and is stumped in business-like fashion by the keeper, who is having a fabulous tour! England's innings is subsiding meekly here
Dismissal_text: L Gregory st †Mohammad Rizwan b Imad Wasim 2 (3b 0x4 0x6) SR: 66.66

Commentary: fired in on the stumps and worked behind square on the leg side
lobbed up on the stumps, Billing clips through midwicket
gives it a bit more flight, Jordan tucks it cautiously off his legs and Imad hares after it, throws it completely in the wrong direction - slippery as a bar of soap - but the damage is only one
starts over the wicket and on the pads, Jordan deflects it fine off the pads
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Jordan, 4 leg byes

Commentary: appeal for a leg-side catch, but Michael Burns signals wide... Pakistan review, Amir in particular was convinced there was something on it. But Jordan has in fact missed it by the width of at least another bat
